the hunted is a 1995 american martial-arts thriller film written and directed by j. f. lawton in his mainstream directorial debut , and starring christopher lambert , john lone , joan chen , yoshio harada and yoko shimada .   lambert plays paul racine , an american businessman who by accident earns the wrath of a ninja clan led by lone 's character , kinjo .   the film was shot in nagoya , japan , and vancouver , canada on a $ 25 million budget , and premiered in february 1995 , taking in $ 6.6 million in u.s. box office .   most critic reviews found the plot clichéed and the acting unconvincing , while some praised harada 's performance as samurai ijuro takeda , racine 's protector and kinjo 's sworn enemy .   the critically well-received soundtrack featured music by the japanese taiko troupe kodō , which pervades the film .   the hunted was released on vhs , dvd and blu-ray .